<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4933.2.3>
    bibo:endPage "240" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2021-02-19" ;
    bibo:startPage "211" ;
    bibo:volume "4933" ;
    dc:creator "Donnellan, Stephen C.; Catalano, Sarah R.; Pederson, Stephen; Mitchell, Kieren J.; Suhendran, Aidan; Price, Luke C.; Doughty, Paul; Richards, Stephen J." ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Revision of the Litoria watjulumensis (Anura: Pelodryadidae) group from the Australian monsoonal tropics, including the resurrection of L. spaldingi" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550240>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550242>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550244>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550234>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550236>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550232>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550246> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550240>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Images of Litoria watjulumensis in life: A) male NTM R37217 from East Baines Crossing, Gregory NP, NT [D. Trembath], B) female NTM R37218 from East Baines Crossing, Gregory NP, NT [D. Trembath], C) male, WAM R162511 Grotto Creek, WA [P. Doughty]; D) WAM R173850 from Theda Station, WA [R. Ellis]; E) male, no voucher, from El Questro, WA [S. Mahony]; F) male, WAM R162598 Mount Leake, WA [P. Doughty]." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4550240/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550242>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Images of thighs in life showing color and pattern of Litoria spaldingi: A) WAM R23886 holotype; B) NTM R36092; C) NTM R36092 Darwin, NT; and Litoria watjulumensis: D) WAM R11896 lectotype; E) WAM R171464 Prince Regent River Nature Reserve; WA; F) WAM R164940 Bigge Island, WA." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4550242/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550244>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Images of the preserved type of Hyla latopalmata watjulumensis, WAM R11896. A) dorsal, B) ventral, C) lateral head, D) palmar, and E) plantar views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4550244/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550234>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Phylogram of relationships among mitochondrial ND4 sequences of ground hylid group of Litoria. Numerical values at nodes represent ML bootstrap proportions (left) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (right)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4550234/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550236>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Phylogram of relationships among the nuclear PTPN12 sequences of ground hylid group of Litoria. Numerical values at nodes represent ML bootstrap proportions (left) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (right)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4550236/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550232>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Map showing the distribution of museum vouchers for the Litoria watjulumensis group (open small circles), vouchers that were analysed for morphometrics (solid black circles) and the collection locations for material that was analysed with molecular genetic techniques (orange [western] and blue [eastern] large triangles). Type locations for Hyla latopalmata watjulumensis and Hyla spaldingi are indicated by W and S respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4550232/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4550246>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. A) Waveform (top) and spectrogram (bottom) of part of a call sequence from Litoria watjulumensis (WAM R162508) recorded at The Grotto near Wyndham, WA, at a temperature of 28.3°C. Note the abrupt doubling of note repetition rate approximately 2/3 of the way through the long call. B) Waveform (top) and spectrogram (bottom) of part of a call sequence from a Litoria spaldingi (FrogID #6921) recorded 20 km southeast of Darwin, Northern Territory, illustrating 15 short calls and one long call (see text). Spectrograms generated using fast-Fourier Transform of 1024 points, 50% overlap, and Hamming Window." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4550246/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

